{
    "ocr_text": "Mr. V. B. Garber, President, Brotherhood of Locomotive Firemen and Enginemen, Peoria, Illinois.

Dear Sir and Brother:

I am just in receipt of your courteous invitation to attend the Twelfth Biennial Convention of the Brotherhood of Locomotive Firemen and Enginemen, which will convene on Monday evening, June 6th, at the Auditorium in St. Paul, Minnesota. I beg to assure you of my appreciation of the courtesy of your invitation.

That I should be greatly pleased to be able to accept your invitation should go without saying. It would indeed afford me great pleasure to have the opportunity of meeting and greeting the officers and delegates to your convention, but I regret to say that my engagements are of such a character as to make it impossible for me to do so. You will permit me, however, to express the sincere hope for a successful and profitable convention.

With kind regards and hoping to hear from you from time to time whenever convenient, I am,

Fraternally yours,

President, American Federation of Labor.",
